edback in balancing them further before we send them live.'<br><br>The most controversial changes include:<br><br>- Mana Burn (Wiz) and Life Burn (Nec) now cap at 10,000 damage. <br>- Mana Burn (Wiz) and Life Burn (Nec) can no longer deal a critical blast. <br>- Dire Charmed (Enc, Dru, Nec) pets can no longer be buffed. <br>- Dire Charmed (Enc, Dru, Nec) pets will now only deal 66% of their normal damage. <br>- Dire Charm Spells will now have a small chance to be resisted. <br>- Healing Gift will now use up double mana when a critical heal succesfully lands. <br><br>For a full list of the complete changes be sure to read the full announcement. <br><br>Click <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4205">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for details. <p><center><br>Level 60 Warlock of the Nameless</center><marquee>Jlorjallag!</marquee></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/userinade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serinade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 12:28:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3030.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alternate Advancment Balancing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Dire Charmed (Enc, Dru, Nec) pets will now only deal 66% of their normal damage<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>So what they basically are going to be like a normal summoned pet you can't buff? <p>58 Troubadour Of Nameless<br><i>"Its Gods responsibility to forgive Bin Laden.<br>It's our responsibility to arrange the meeting."<br><b>US Marine Corps</b></i><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134927">Cha